answer_baseline:
In the latest FastAPI docs template, if you’re looping over sponsor groups and want to keep the old condition:

```jinja2
{% if user.login not in sponsors_badge.logins %}
```

you should apply that check inside the nested loop for each sponsor item.

For example, if the template now looks something like this:

```jinja2
{% for group in sponsor_groups %}
  {% for user in group.users %}
    ...
  {% endfor %}
{% endfor %}
```

then preserve the old behavior like this:

```jinja2
{% for group in sponsor_groups %}
  {% for user in group.users %}
    {% if user.login not in sponsors_badge.logins %}
      <!-- render user -->
    {% endif %}
  {% endfor %}
{% endfor %}
```

If `sponsors_badge.logins` is itself defined per group, use the group-specific variable instead:

```jinja2
{% for group in sponsor_groups %}
  {% for user in group.users %}
    {% if user.login not in group.sponsors_badge.logins %}
      <!-- render user -->
    {% endif %}
  {% endfor %}
{% endfor %}
```

If you want, I can also help adapt the exact FastAPI template snippet from the current docs repo.

